Deep Learning · Cybersecurity · Explainable AI

Overview

This project focuses on building a deep-learning-based Intrusion Detection System (IDS) to identify malicious network traffic and abnormal behavior in a distributed environment. The system emphasizes both detection accuracy and interpretability to support reliable security decision-making.

Key Features

Classifies network traffic as benign or malicious using deep learning models

Detects anomalies by analyzing traffic patterns and attack indicators

Integrates Explainable AI techniques to interpret model predictions

Improves transparency and trust in automated security alerts

What I Built

Designed and implemented a deep learning pipeline for intrusion detection on network traffic data

Analyzed network behavior to identify anomalies, attack signatures, and threat patterns

Integrated SHAP (Explainable AI) to explain model outputs and highlight influential features

Evaluated model performance and iteratively refined detection logic

Technical Learnings

Practical exposure to cybersecurity concepts, including anomaly detection and threat classification

Improved understanding of distributed systems behavior and system reliability

Hands-on experience balancing model accuracy with interpretability in security-critical systems

Tech Stack

Languages: Python

Concepts: Deep Learning, Anomaly Detection, Explainable AI

Tools & Libraries: SHAP, ML/DL frameworks

Domain: Cybersecurity, Network Traffic Analysis
